 BLT (blit, very rarely belt) [based on the PDP-10 block transfer
instruction; confusing to users of the PDP-11] 1. v. To transfer a large
contiguous package of informa- tion from one place to another. 2. THE BIG
BLT: n. Shuffling operation on the PDP-10 under some operating systems that
consumes a significant amount of computer time. 3. (usually pronounced B-L-T)
n. Sandwich con- taining bacon, lettuce, and tomato.